text: Y’all better get right with Spirit...

author: Empress JaShada
text:
When you decide to finally make that list of your “perfect” person, how many of those things do you currently possess and are willing to give/compromise on? 

Don’t expect someone else to have/be what you aren’t willing to do/change.

author: Empress JaShada
text: Become the person you want to date. If you couldn’t handle me treating you the way you treat me, don’t expect me to just accept it because you wouldn’t.  It goes both ways. And make no excuses because there is always a choice.

author: Empress JaShada
text:
Don’t ever want something so bad that you lose yourself in the process. This goes for EVERYTHING. 

When you start off on a lie (not being true to who you are) that is how it will continue, and you will in fact suffer. 

Always honor your true self first ❤️

author: Empress JaShada
text: I don’t think we often see things are they are but rather we see them as WE are. Neither observation is right or wrong. It just is what it is.

author: Empress JaShada
text: The transference of trauma is real. And for that we must heal. Ain’t gonna lie to you like healing is easy because it’s not. But it’s necessary. For you, your kids, future generations, and all of the people you come in contact with.

author: Empress JaShada
text: Sometimes our blessings don’t show up in the way we would expect them to. Let go of the expectation that it will. If it is causing you discomfort because of its “appearance” check in with your feelings instead. Ask God for clarity✨

author: Empress JaShada
text: Don’t mistake my openness for closeness✨ I don’t allow many people to get close to me 😌

author: Empress JaShada
text:
Hard truths...

Sometimes the purpose/lesson we serve in other people’s lives can and will hurt us in the process 😢

author: Empress JaShada
text: Integrity is knowing you could do something but choosing not to because you know deep down inside it’s not right. I’m realizing a lot of people lack that 🥴

author: Empress JaShada
text: Remember you are God in the flesh, don’t ever let another person tell you who you are.

author: Empress JaShada
text: The loss of someone who hurt or betrayed you is still a lost. It’s okay to grieve. Just don’t forget they showed you who they are.

author: Empress JaShada
text: Learn to draw inspiration from disappointment. That’s what you call alchemy. And we are all capable of it✨

author: Empress JaShada
text: Holding onto a grudge can block you from receiving a blessing. Don’t hold yourself hostage to the past that you miss out on a better future. Forgive and release.

author: Empress JaShada
text: Being an understanding person is not always an easy thing to do but it protects your peace. Once you understand most people are out here operating from their traumas you learn compassion. This in no way means you have to put up with it, you just understand.

author: Empress JaShada
text: What another person does almost never has anything to do with you. We all have choices in life and they chose to do what they did. So now you have to choose what’s best for you and start holding people accountable for how they make you feel whether directly or indirectly.

author: Empress JaShada
text:
My job as a healer is to teach you self-empowerment. I will provide you with the tools necessary to start your journey but I never want you to become dependent on me. Your journey is your own. 

Signed,
A Healer that Healed Herself ❤️

author: Empress JaShada
text: One thing about it, God is always sending us signs. Through our own suffering, symbols, numbers, synchronicities, and sometimes other people. But we don’t always choose to recognize them. And for that we are choosing to suffer.

author: Empress JaShada
text:
Having a “lack” mentality leads to fear. Fear leads to you operating on a low vibration. And nothing good comes from living in fear. Shift your mindset to abundance and you will vibrate higher✨

Affirmation: “I lack nothing. All that I need I have within me. I am abundant.”

author: Empress JaShada
text:
Grand Rising🌞

Did you wake up, thank God, and set your intention for the day?

Expressing gratitude regularly and intentional living can drastically change your life. Try it out✨

author: Empress JaShada
text: In order to hear your higher self, you have to eliminate the distractions✨

author: Empress JaShada
text: Listen to your higher self. It knows the way✨

author: Empress JaShada
text: Believe you are worthy of better and you will attract better. If not, you will continue to self-sabotage.

author: Empress JaShada
text:
Grand Rising✨

Let this be a sign to you today so that you may have the courage to let things go that no longer serve you✨

Don’t get comfortable in the uncomfortable✨

author: Empress JaShada
text: Day 1 of this month’s/moon cycle fast✨

author: Empress JaShada
text:
Shadow work question of the day...

Are you really genuinely happy or are you just pretending?

author: Empress JaShada
text: With “time” you either get better or worse. Choose wisely✨

author: Empress JaShada
text:
Don’t be easily impressed...
 Easily impressed=easily manipulated. Keep your wits about you 😉

author: Empress JaShada
text:
If you’ve been praying and manifesting a better life for yourself and things around you are suddenly changing, it’s working... 

 The question is...Do you really want it?

author: Empress JaShada
text: Change and growth is on the horizon. Once the dust settles, there you’ll find clarity.

author: Empress JaShada
text: IT’S LIKE...WHEN ONE OR MULTIPLE  AREA(S) OF YOUR LIFE IS REALLY  THRIVING SPIRIT GOTTA SHAKE SOME SHIT UP 😅 LIKE LET ME SEE IF YOU’RE ABOUT ALL THAT YOU SAY YOU ARE. Let the games begin...

author: Empress JaShada
text: Anybody else feel like Spirit does the most sometimes? Not complaining just saying 😒

author: Empress JaShada
text: Money can’t buy you your way out of karmic debt. You pay for that with pieces of your soul.
